    {"q": "How do I set up a secure MQTT connection with TLS?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nSecure MQTT with TLS requires:\n1. TLS/SSL certificates (CA cert, optionally client certs)\n2. Proper port (8883 instead of 1883)\n3. WiFiClientSecure instead of WiFiClient\n4. Certificate verification\n<|/thinking|>\n\nHere's how to set up secure MQTT with TLS on ESP32:\n\n```cpp\n#include <WiFi.h>\n#include <WiFiClientSecure.h>\n#include <PubSubClient.h>\n\nconst char* mqtt_server = \"your-broker.com\";\nconst int mqtt_port = 8883;\n\nconst char* ca_cert = R\"EOF(\n-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\n... your CA certificate here ...\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\n)EOF\";\n\nWiFiClientSecure espClient;\nPubSubClient client(espClient);\n\nvoid setup() {\n  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);\n  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) delay(500);\n  \n  espClient.setCACert(ca_cert);\n  client.setServer(mqtt_server, mqtt_port);\n  client.connect(\"ESP32SecureClient\");\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement MQTT Last Will and Testament (LWT)?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nLWT in MQTT allows automatic notification when client disconnects unexpectedly:\n1. Broker publishes the will message on client timeout\n2. Configured during connection\n3. Useful for device status monitoring\n<|/thinking|>\n\nImplement MQTT LWT for device monitoring:\n\n```cpp\nconst char* status_topic = \"devices/esp32/status\";\nconst char* will_message = \"offline\";\n\nvoid reconnect() {\n  while (!client.connected()) {\n    // Connect with LWT: topic, QoS, retain, message\n    if (client.connect(\"ESP32Device\", NULL, NULL,\n                       status_topic, 1, true, will_message)) {\n      client.publish(status_topic, \"online\", true);\n    } else {\n      delay(5000);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nIf ESP32 loses connection, broker publishes \"offline\" automatically."},
    {"q": "How do I subscribe to multiple MQTT topics with wildcards?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nMQTT wildcards:\n1. + matches single level (sensors/+/temp)\n2. # matches multiple levels (sensors/#)\n3. Callback needs to parse actual topic\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nvoid callback(char* topic, byte* payload, unsigned int length) {\n  String topicStr = String(topic);\n  String message = \"\";\n  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) message += (char)payload[i];\n  \n  // Parse topic: sensors/room1/temperature\n  if (topicStr.startsWith(\"sensors/\")) {\n    int slash = topicStr.indexOf('/', 8);\n    String room = topicStr.substring(8, slash);\n    String sensor = topicStr.substring(slash + 1);\n    Serial.printf(\"Room: %s, Sensor: %s, Value: %s\\n\",\n                  room.c_str(), sensor.c_str(), message.c_str());\n  }\n}\n\nvoid setup() {\n  client.subscribe(\"sensors/+/temperature\");  // All temps\n  client.subscribe(\"sensors/#\");  // Everything\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement MQTT retained messages for device state?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nRetained messages:\n1. Broker stores the last message on a topic\n2. New subscribers immediately receive current state\n3. Set retain flag to true when publishing\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nconst char* state_topic = \"home/light1/state\";\nbool lightState = false;\n\nvoid publishState() {\n  // retain = true, new subscribers get current state\n  client.publish(state_topic, lightState ? \"ON\" : \"OFF\", true);\n}\n\nvoid callback(char* topic, byte* payload, unsigned int length) {\n  String command = \"\";\n  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) command += (char)payload[i];\n  \n  if (command == \"ON\") {\n    lightState = true;\n    digitalWrite(LED_PIN, HIGH);\n  } else {\n    lightState = false;\n    digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW);\n  }\n  publishState();  // Update retained state\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I build an MQTT bridge between two brokers?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nMQTT bridge connects brokers for:\n1. Local to cloud sync\n2. Network segmentation\n3. Redundancy\nESP32 can bridge between two brokers.\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nWiFiClient localClient, cloudClient;\nPubSubClient localMqtt(localClient);\nPubSubClient cloudMqtt(cloudClient);\n\nvoid localCallback(char* topic, byte* payload, unsigned int length) {\n  String cloudTopic = \"bridge/\" + String(topic);\n  cloudMqtt.publish(cloudTopic.c_str(), payload, length);\n}\n\nvoid cloudCallback(char* topic, byte* payload, unsigned int length) {\n  String localTopic = String(topic).substring(7);  // Remove \"bridge/\"\n  localMqtt.publish(localTopic.c_str(), payload, length);\n}\n\nvoid setup() {\n  localMqtt.setServer(\"192.168.1.100\", 1883);\n  localMqtt.setCallback(localCallback);\n  localMqtt.subscribe(\"sensors/#\");\n  \n  cloudMqtt.setServer(\"broker.hivemq.com\", 1883);\n  cloudMqtt.setCallback(cloudCallback);\n  cloudMqtt.subscribe(\"bridge/commands/#\");\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I handle MQTT reconnection gracefully?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nGraceful MQTT reconnection needs:\n1. Non-blocking reconnect logic\n2. Exponential backoff\n3. Resubscribe after reconnect\n4. Status feedback\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nunsigned long lastReconnectAttempt = 0;\nint reconnectDelay = 1000;  // Start with 1 second\n\nbool reconnect() {\n  if (client.connect(\"ESP32Client\")) {\n    client.subscribe(\"commands/#\");\n    client.publish(\"status\", \"online\", true);\n    reconnectDelay = 1000;  // Reset delay\n    return true;\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  if (!client.connected()) {\n    unsigned long now = millis();\n    if (now - lastReconnectAttempt > reconnectDelay) {\n      lastReconnectAttempt = now;\n      if (!reconnect()) {\n        // Exponential backoff, max 30 seconds\n        reconnectDelay = min(reconnectDelay * 2, 30000);\n      }\n    }\n  } else {\n    client.loop();\n  }\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement MQTT message queuing when offline?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nOffline message queuing:\n1. Store messages locally when disconnected\n2. Send queued messages after reconnect\n3. Use circular buffer to limit memory\n4. Handle message expiry\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\n#include <queue>\n\nstruct QueuedMessage {\n  String topic;\n  String payload;\n  unsigned long timestamp;\n};\n\nstd::queue<QueuedMessage> messageQueue;\nconst int MAX_QUEUE = 50;\nconst unsigned long MESSAGE_TTL = 300000;  // 5 minutes\n\nvoid queueMessage(String topic, String payload) {\n  if (messageQueue.size() >= MAX_QUEUE) messageQueue.pop();\n  messageQueue.push({topic, payload, millis()});\n}\n\nvoid publishOrQueue(String topic, String payload) {\n  if (client.connected()) {\n    client.publish(topic.c_str(), payload.c_str());\n  } else {\n    queueMessage(topic, payload);\n  }\n}\n\nvoid flushQueue() {\n  while (!messageQueue.empty() && client.connected()) {\n    QueuedMessage msg = messageQueue.front();\n    if (millis() - msg.timestamp < MESSAGE_TTL) {\n      client.publish(msg.topic.c_str(), msg.payload.c_str());\n    }\n    messageQueue.pop();\n  }\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement JSON payloads with MQTT on ESP32?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nJSON with MQTT on ESP32:\n1. Use ArduinoJson library\n2. Serialize sensor data to JSON\n3. Parse incoming JSON commands\n4. Watch memory with StaticJsonDocument\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\n#include <ArduinoJson.h>\n\nvoid publishSensorData(float temp, float humidity, int light) {\n  StaticJsonDocument<200> doc;\n  doc[\"temperature\"] = temp;\n  doc[\"humidity\"] = humidity;\n  doc[\"light\"] = light;\n  doc[\"timestamp\"] = millis();\n  \n  char buffer[200];\n  serializeJson(doc, buffer);\n  client.publish(\"sensors/data\", buffer);\n}\n\nvoid callback(char* topic, byte* payload, unsigned int length) {\n  StaticJsonDocument<200> doc;\n  DeserializationError error = deserializeJson(doc, payload, length);\n  \n  if (!error) {\n    const char* action = doc[\"action\"];\n    int value = doc[\"value\"] | 0;\n    \n    if (strcmp(action, \"setLED\") == 0) {\n      analogWrite(LED_PIN, value);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement MQTT message throttling to avoid flooding?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nMessage throttling prevents:\n1. Broker overload\n2. Network congestion\n3. Rate limit violations\nImplement with minimum interval between publishes.\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nclass ThrottledPublisher {\n  unsigned long lastPublish = 0;\n  unsigned long minInterval;\n  String lastTopic, lastPayload;\n  bool pending = false;\n  \npublic:\n  ThrottledPublisher(unsigned long interval) : minInterval(interval) {}\n  \n  void publish(String topic, String payload) {\n    unsigned long now = millis();\n    if (now - lastPublish >= minInterval) {\n      client.publish(topic.c_str(), payload.c_str());\n      lastPublish = now;\n      pending = false;\n    } else {\n      lastTopic = topic;\n      lastPayload = payload;\n      pending = true;\n    }\n  }\n  \n  void update() {\n    if (pending && millis() - lastPublish >= minInterval) {\n      publish(lastTopic, lastPayload);\n    }\n  }\n};\n\nThrottledPublisher throttle(1000);  // Max 1 msg/second\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement MQTT authentication with username and password?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nMQTT authentication:\n1. Pass username/password in connect()\n2. Store credentials securely\n3. Use with TLS for security\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nconst char* mqtt_user = \"device01\";\nconst char* mqtt_pass = \"secretpassword\";\n\nvoid reconnect() {\n  while (!client.connected()) {\n    // Connect with authentication\n    if (client.connect(\"ESP32Client\", mqtt_user, mqtt_pass)) {\n      Serial.println(\"Connected with auth\");\n      client.subscribe(\"commands/#\");\n    } else {\n      Serial.print(\"Auth failed, rc=\");\n      Serial.println(client.state());\n      delay(5000);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Security tip:** Store credentials in NVS or use environment variables during flashing. Never hardcode in production."},
