    {"q": "How do I set up LoRaWAN with The Things Network (TTN)?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nLoRaWAN with TTN requires:\n1. TTN account and application\n2. Device registration (OTAA preferred)\n3. LMIC or RadioLib library\n4. Credentials: AppEUI, DevEUI, AppKey\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\n#include <lmic.h>\n#include <hal/hal.h>\n\n// From TTN Console\nstatic const u1_t APPEUI[8] = { 0x00, ... };\nstatic const u1_t DEVEUI[8] = { 0x00, ... };\nstatic const u1_t APPKEY[16] = { 0x00, ... };\n\nvoid os_getArtEui(u1_t* buf) { memcpy_P(buf, APPEUI, 8); }\nvoid os_getDevEui(u1_t* buf) { memcpy_P(buf, DEVEUI, 8); }\nvoid os_getDevKey(u1_t* buf) { memcpy_P(buf, APPKEY, 16); }\n\nconst lmic_pinmap lmic_pins = {\n  .nss = 18, .rst = 14, .dio = {26, 33, 32}\n};\n\nvoid onEvent(ev_t ev) {\n  if (ev == EV_JOINED) Serial.println(\"Joined TTN!\");\n}\n\nvoid setup() {\n  os_init();\n  LMIC_reset();\n  LMIC_startJoining();\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I maximize LoRa range?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nMaximizing LoRa range:\n1. Higher spreading factor (SF12)\n2. Lower bandwidth (125kHz)\n3. Maximum TX power\n4. Good antenna placement\nTrade-off: longer range = slower speed.\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nvoid setup() {\n  LoRa.begin(915E6);\n  \n  // Maximum range settings:\n  LoRa.setSpreadingFactor(12);     // SF12 = longest range\n  LoRa.setSignalBandwidth(125E3);  // 125kHz = best sensitivity\n  LoRa.setCodingRate4(8);          // 4/8 = max error correction\n  LoRa.setTxPower(20);             // 20 dBm max\n  LoRa.enableCrc();\n  \n  // Expected: 10-15km rural, 2-5km urban\n  // Data rate: ~293 bps (very slow)\n}\n```\n\n**Tips:** Use proper antenna, mount high, avoid metal enclosures."},
    {"q": "How do I implement bidirectional LoRa communication?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nBidirectional LoRa needs:\n1. Request-response protocol\n2. Collision avoidance\n3. Acknowledgment system\n4. Timeout handling\n<|/thinking|>\n\n**Node A (sender):**\n```cpp\nbool waitingForAck = false;\nunsigned long lastSend = 0;\n\nvoid loop() {\n  if (!waitingForAck && millis() - lastSend > 5000) {\n    LoRa.beginPacket();\n    LoRa.print(\"REQ:\" + String(msgCount++));\n    LoRa.endPacket();\n    waitingForAck = true;\n    lastSend = millis();\n  }\n  \n  int size = LoRa.parsePacket();\n  if (size) {\n    String resp = \"\";\n    while (LoRa.available()) resp += (char)LoRa.read();\n    if (resp.startsWith(\"ACK:\")) waitingForAck = false;\n  }\n  \n  if (waitingForAck && millis() - lastSend > 2000) {\n    waitingForAck = false;  // Timeout, retry\n  }\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I create a LoRa mesh network?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nLoRa mesh allows:\n1. Extended range via relaying\n2. Self-healing topology\n3. Need addressing and routing\n4. Track seen messages to avoid loops\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\n#define NODE_ID 1\n#define MAX_HOPS 3\n\nstruct Message {\n  uint8_t src, dest, hops, msgId;\n  char payload[32];\n};\n\nuint8_t seenMsgs[10];\nint seenIdx = 0;\n\nbool alreadySeen(uint8_t src, uint8_t id) {\n  uint16_t key = (src << 8) | id;\n  for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++)\n    if (seenMsgs[i] == key) return true;\n  seenMsgs[seenIdx++ % 10] = key;\n  return false;\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  int size = LoRa.parsePacket();\n  if (size == sizeof(Message)) {\n    Message msg;\n    LoRa.readBytes((uint8_t*)&msg, sizeof(msg));\n    \n    if (alreadySeen(msg.src, msg.msgId)) return;\n    \n    if (msg.dest == NODE_ID)\n      Serial.printf(\"Got: %s\\n\", msg.payload);\n    \n    if (msg.hops < MAX_HOPS && msg.dest != NODE_ID) {\n      msg.hops++;\n      delay(random(100, 500));\n      LoRa.beginPacket();\n      LoRa.write((uint8_t*)&msg, sizeof(msg));\n      LoRa.endPacket();\n    }\n  }\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement LoRa frequency hopping?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nFrequency hopping:\n1. Improves reliability\n2. Required by some regulations\n3. Both nodes must sync\n4. Use deterministic sequence\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nconst long frequencies[] = {\n  902300000, 902500000, 902700000, 902900000,\n  903100000, 903300000, 903500000, 903700000\n};\nconst int numChannels = 8;\nconst int hopInterval = 400;  // ms\n\nuint32_t seed = 12345;\nuint32_t nextRandom() {\n  seed = seed * 1103515245 + 12345;\n  return seed;\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  // Sync hopping based on time slot\n  unsigned long slot = millis() / hopInterval;\n  seed = 12345 + slot;\n  int channel = nextRandom() % numChannels;\n  \n  LoRa.setFrequency(frequencies[channel]);\n  \n  // TX/RX on current channel\n  int size = LoRa.parsePacket();\n  // ...\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I implement AES encryption with LoRa?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nAES encryption for LoRa:\n1. Use AES-128 or AES-256\n2. Encrypt payload before sending\n3. Share key securely\n4. Add message authentication\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\n#include <AES.h>\n#include <CBC.h>\n\nCBC<AES128> aes;\nbyte key[16] = {0x00, 0x01, 0x02, ...};  // Shared secret\nbyte iv[16];  // Initialize randomly\n\nvoid sendEncrypted(const char* plaintext, int len) {\n  // Generate random IV\n  for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) iv[i] = random(256);\n  \n  byte encrypted[64];\n  aes.setKey(key, 16);\n  aes.setIV(iv, 16);\n  aes.encrypt(encrypted, (byte*)plaintext, len);\n  \n  LoRa.beginPacket();\n  LoRa.write(iv, 16);  // Send IV first\n  LoRa.write(encrypted, len);\n  LoRa.endPacket();\n}\n\nvoid receiveDecrypt() {\n  byte iv[16], encrypted[64], decrypted[64];\n  LoRa.readBytes(iv, 16);\n  int len = LoRa.available();\n  LoRa.readBytes(encrypted, len);\n  \n  aes.setKey(key, 16);\n  aes.setIV(iv, 16);\n  aes.decrypt(decrypted, encrypted, len);\n}\n```"},
    {"q": "How do I send sensor data efficiently over LoRa?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nEfficient LoRa data:\n1. Use binary format, not text\n2. Pack data tightly\n3. Minimize payload size\n4. Use appropriate data types\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\nstruct SensorPacket {\n  uint8_t nodeId;\n  int16_t temperature;  // 0.01°C resolution\n  uint16_t humidity;    // 0.01% resolution\n  uint16_t battery;     // mV\n  uint32_t timestamp;\n} __attribute__((packed));  // 11 bytes total\n\nvoid sendSensorData(float temp, float hum, float batt) {\n  SensorPacket pkt;\n  pkt.nodeId = NODE_ID;\n  pkt.temperature = (int16_t)(temp * 100);  // 25.50°C -> 2550\n  pkt.humidity = (uint16_t)(hum * 100);\n  pkt.battery = (uint16_t)(batt * 1000);\n  pkt.timestamp = millis() / 1000;\n  \n  LoRa.beginPacket();\n  LoRa.write((uint8_t*)&pkt, sizeof(pkt));\n  LoRa.endPacket();\n}\n```\n\n11 bytes vs 50+ bytes for JSON = 5x more efficient."},
    {"q": "How do I implement LoRa with sleep mode for battery?", "a": "<|thinking|>\nLoRa + sleep for battery:\n1. Send data, then deep sleep\n2. Wake on timer or interrupt\n3. Reinitialize LoRa after wake\n4. Power down LoRa module\n<|/thinking|>\n\n```cpp\n#include <SPI.h>\n#include <LoRa.h>\n\n#define SLEEP_SECONDS 300  // 5 minutes\n\nvoid setup() {\n  esp_sleep_enable_timer_wakeup(SLEEP_SECONDS * 1000000ULL);\n  \n  LoRa.begin(915E6);\n  \n  // Read sensor and send\n  float temp = readTemperature();\n  LoRa.beginPacket();\n  LoRa.print(temp);\n  LoRa.endPacket();\n  \n  // Wait for TX complete\n  delay(100);\n  \n  // Power down LoRa\n  LoRa.sleep();\n  \n  // Enter deep sleep\n  esp_deep_sleep_start();\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  // Never reached\n}\n```\n\nCurrent: TX ~120mA, Sleep ~10µA. Average < 1mA with 1% duty cycle."},
